<http://model.geneontology.org/R-HSA-9818027/R-HSA-9818027>
        a       <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual> , <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/GO_0008150> ;
        <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment>
                "Subpathway representing cytoprotective genes regulated by NFE2L2 (NRF2). NFE2L2 is well-studied for its role in oxidative stress where it gets activated by ROS and then induces a plethora of gene expression regulation the oxidative damage. It induces genes/enzymes that regulate the phase 2 detoxification system (eg. GSTs and Glutathione system), ROS scavenging (SODs,PRDX1 ) and cytoprotection (HO1) by regulating inflammation and tissue damage (Tonelli et al, 2018; Shaw et al, 2020)" ;
        <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label>
                "NFE2L2 regulating anti-oxidant/detoxification enzymes" ;
        <http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/contributor>
                "GOC:reactome_curators" , "Edited: Tiwari, Krishna, 2022-10-10" , "Authored: Tiwari, Krishna, 2022-10-10" ;
        <http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/date>
                "2026-04-09" ;
